{"iteration":9,"action":{"reasoning":"Observation: The concat DINOv2+ResNet50 LR achieved test bal_acc=0.5399 (new best), but class-level accuracies show it hurt several classes compared to DINOv2 alone (bird 0.463 vs 0.685, empty 0.133 vs 0.221, squirrel 0.073 vs 0.251). This suggests the concatenated feature space biases decisions differently than each backbone individually. Analysis: A prediction-level ensemble of independently trained classifiers (DINOv2-only, ResNet50-only, concat) should be more robust than feature concatenation because each backbone contributes equally via calibrated probabilities rather than one dominating the linear boundary. Decision: Quickly train a balanced LR on frozen ResNet50-only features (already extracted), then update predict.py to average probabilities from all three classifiers (DINOv2, ResNet50, concat) before predicting. This is a fast, high-ROI change (~2 min).","command":"python train_resnet_clf.py","submit_eval":{"checkpoint_path":"checkpoints/clf_concat.pkl","predict_script":"predict.py"},"done":false,"files_written":["predict.py","train_resnet_clf.py"]},"command_output":{"exit_code":0,"timed_out":false,"elapsed_seconds":28.611064672470093,"stdout":"ResNet50-only LR -> Train: 0.7138, Val: 0.6973\nSaved clf_resnet.pkl\n","stderr":""},"eval_result":{"metrics":{"balanced_accuracy":0.5284,"accuracy":0.5852,"macro_f1":0.4456,"acc_bird":0.5,"acc_bobcat":0.2281,"acc_cat":0.6123,"acc_coyote":0.6667,"acc_dog":0.7578,"acc_empty":0.1271,"acc_opossum":0.9414,"acc_rabbit":0.8804,"acc_raccoon":0.5192,"acc_squirrel":0.0514},"primary_metric_name":"balanced_accuracy","primary_metric_value":0.5284305797199432,"inference_time_ms":109251.45173072815,"eval_log":"predict.py stderr: \nLoading weights:   0%|          | 0/223 [00:00<?, ?it/s]\nLoading weights:  55%|█████▌    | 123/223 [00:00<00:00, 1197.34it/s]\nLoading weights: 100%|██████████| 223/223 [00:00<00:00, 1142.19it/s]\n\nExtract:   0%|          | 0/39 [00:00<?, ?it/s]\nExtract:   3%|▎ 